data.description: Situated just 3 miles from I-376 in the historic railway town of New Galilee-and just 45 minutes by car to downtown Pittsburgh-this home was built in 1880 and was completely renovated in 2016. A two bedroom house with high ceilings, this home also has a bonus room upstairs which could be a third bedroom. The well-maintained kitchen and living room looks out over back deck and enclosed rear yard.  Front deck overlooks the the beautiful hamlet. Hunters, campers, hikers and fisherfolk will appreciate the closeness of near-by parks, wetlands, and gamelands.  Check out the virtual tour of book a showing of this unique home today!
